Living at Curry College: Play a key role on campus, create strong relationships with peers and access an abundance of opportunities while living on campus.

Leadership Programs at Curry college: The President’s Leadership Program (PLP) at Curry College is made up of a highly selective group of talented, driven, compassionate, and accomplished students and is designed to inspire and foster leaders of tomorrow. The President’s Leadership Program prepares students for a life of leadership, civic responsibility, and career success through a range of activities, workshops, and events just for PLP students both inside and outside the classroom.

Social Achievement in Learning (SAIL) Program at Curry College: The Social Achievement in Learning (SAIL) program is designed for academically capable students with neurodiverse profiles who benefit from individualized support to reach their full potential in a college environment.
PAL Academic Experience: PAL provides personalized academic support tailored to your needs, offering either one-on-one or small group sessions.

Curry Connectors: Curry Connectors are our partners who are seeking to develop a diverse workforce pipeline and who are also interested in supporting and participating in industry-relevant academic programming such as mentorships, class visits, class consulting projects, networking events, or career fairs.
Curry College is a private liberal arts college in Milton, Massachusetts, offering a supportive and dynamic learning environment that fosters academic, personal, and professional growth for students.

Schedule a Visit at Curry College: Visit the Campus of the Curry College. Curry College is just 7 miles from Boston, but our wooded, 131-acre campus feels like a world away.
Explore Curry College before the Admission: Check out Curry College even before you make your first visit!

International Student Admission at Curry College: Apply at Curry College as the International Students.

International Student Orientation Day at Curry College: International Student Orientation, where you’ll meet other international students, learn about life on campus and Boston and get a head start on preparing for college classes.
Undergraduate Tuition and Financial Aid at Curry College: A Curry College education is an investment in the person you want to become — and the life that you want to live.
Meal Plan Accommodations at Curry College: Curry College takes your dietary needs seriously and we understand that your health and safety are most important to a successful college experience.

Housing Accommodations at Curry College: Accessible Housing is available to students at Curry who have disabilities that substantially impact one or more major life activities as they relate to housing.

Emotional Support Animals (ESA) at Curry College: All Emotional Support Animal Documentation must come from an external, licensed provider who oversees the treatment of your diagnosed disability and has an established relationship with you.

Disability Accommodations Abroad at Curry College: The underlying philosophy of Curry College is still to support our students with disabilities as much as possible with their needs as if it did apply abroad.
Curry College Bookstore: Our selection of textbooks, general books, computers, course materials, and supplies will ensure every Curry College student is prepared for success.
Safety at Curry College: The Curry College Department of Public Safety's mission is to provide a safe and secure environment for our entire community.

Dining option at Curry College: Curry College and Sodexo Campus Services work together to give our hard-working Curry students a superior dining experience by providing plenty of nourishing options to suit all preferences and schedules.
